erything is boring and my school mates suck. The only thing that\'s good is the radio channels. Finally I there\'s some good music on the radio. Pretty much the only way to a hold of hip hop and r&amp;b before was to go to the music store which I wasn\'t supposed to go to. Now that music is played on the radio all the time. I\'ve seen other guys in school listening to my favourite song \"Who run the world\" by Beyoncé. I\'m probably gonna talk to that guy tomorrow. He seems cool.</div><div>Cheers,</div><div>Ben</div>',0,'2014-01-21 15:19:43'),(28,48,'Is this what the world has come to? Is there no freedom left in this world? Since when has the white race succumb to the manipulation and taunts of the niggers and chinks!?<br><br>And every school we looked at seemed to somehow be infested with them! Now I have to sit and (Oh _God!) eat with those people!!&nbsp;<br><br>Almost every girl I see here are either tainted or hang out with a bunch of underfucked scums!<br><br>Of all places, why can\'t we move ina place where our freedom is respected? University of Arkansas... here I come!<br>',0,'2014-01-21 15:20:13'),(29,48,'\"Siegtuna\", my parents said. <br>Ever since I was a little boy, they\'d been talking about Siegtuna. <br><br>\"Siegtuna, where svenskhatarna and PK-maffian were tamed.\"<br><div><div><div>\"Siegtuna, where feminazis and immigrants were cuffed to their stoves and brooms.\"<br>\"Siegtuna, where you could get a decent niggerball.\"<br></div><div><br></div><div>\"Siegtuna, the town of Viking Kings, \"<br>\"Siegtuna, the town of swedes.\"</div><div><br></div><div>\"Sigtuna\", the sign said.<br><br><br><br></div></div></div>',0,'2014-01-21 15:22:24'),(30,48,'\"Hanzel, look at all those faces. Filthy. Coloured. Dirty.&nbsp;Animals.&nbsp;Disgusting.\"<div>\"Yes, mother.\"</div><div><br></div><div>I was glancing though the window of our car as we passed&nbsp;the city square, with all it\'s booths and people buying groceries and what nots.&nbsp;</div><div>At the end of the square we passed a booth managed by a young woman.&nbsp;She was the most beautiful human I had ever seen. Her skin rich, like dark chocolate. Her eyes, a colour of warm brown I\'d never seen before.&nbsp;As she looked up she met my gaze, and she smiled.&nbsp;</div><div>A shy smile that lit up her freckles and filled my insides with fireworks.&nbsp;</div><div>I had to meet this girl. Talk to her. Touch her. Hear her voice and give her my heart.&nbsp;</div><div>My heart that already loved her.&nbsp;</div>',0,'2014-01-21 15:22:30'),(31,48,'Trying to talk any sense into my parents at this point is meaningless. It\'s a lost cause, really. I\'m just baffled at how it even got to this point. I honestly don\'t understand it. Maybe it\'s like those times when things happen for seemingly no particular reason; they could as well have turned out completely differently.<div><br></div><div>As it is now, I\'ve just given up in trying. I can\'t wait till I move out and get my own place. They have painted freaking swastikas all over the apartment, for crying out loud. The bathroom door has got a freaking poster of Hitler on it. How am I supposed to have friends over? Ain\'t gonna work. I just hope I can keep any details about my parents away from anyone in this city. But with my loony parents, that\'s going to be difficult. Probably impossible...</div><div><br></div><div>There\'s only one way out. One solution. One ending to this story.</div><div><br></div><div>I have to kill my parents in their sleep.</div><div>Or I could lock them up in the basement.</div><div>But then I\'ll have to feed them and stuff.</div><div>No, I guess I have to kill my parents.</div>',0,'2014-01-21 15:27:04');
